.TH "PEEP" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
peep \- run a command repeatedly on a refreshing screen
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]peep\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[B]\(en\f[R]] \f[I]command\f[R]
[\f[I]args\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs \f[I]command\f[R] repeatedly and displays its output on a
refreshing full\-screen display.
Supports interval polling, file\-watch triggers, diff highlighting,
time\-machine history, and auto\-exit conditions.
.PP
While running, peep responds to keyboard input (see INTERACTIVE
CONTROLS).
Press \f[B]q\f[R] or \f[B]Ctrl+C\f[R] to quit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\(eninterval\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Seconds between runs (default: 2).
.TP
\f[B]\-w\f[R], \f[B]\(enwatch\f[R] \f[I]GLOB\f[R]
Re\-run on file changes matching glob pattern (repeatable).
If \f[B]\-w\f[R] is given without \f[B]\-n\f[R], interval polling is
disabled.
.TP
\f[B]\(endebounce\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Milliseconds to debounce file change events (default: 300).
.TP
\f[B]\(enhistory\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Maximum history snapshots to retain (default: 1000; 0 = unlimited).
.TP
\f[B]\-g\f[R], \f[B]\(enexit\-on\-change\f[R]
Exit when output changes between runs.
.TP
\f[B]\(enexit\-on\-success\f[R]
Exit when the command returns exit code 0.
.TP
\f[B]\-e\f[R], \f[B]\(enexit\-on\-error\f[R]
Exit when the command returns a non\-zero exit code.
.TP
\f[B]\(enexit\-on\-match\f[R] \f[I]PAT\f[R]
Exit when output matches regex \f[I]PAT\f[R] (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R], \f[B]\(endifferences\f[R]
Highlight changed lines between runs.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-gitignore\f[R]
Disable automatic .gitignore filtering for \f[B]\(enwatch\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\(enonce\f[R]
Run once, display output, and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(enno\-header\f[R]
Hide the header lines.
.TP
\f[B]\(enjson\f[R]
JSON summary to stderr on exit.
.TP
\f[B]\(enjson\-output\f[R]
Include the last captured output in JSON (implies \f[B]\(enjson\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(encolor\f[R]
Force coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-color\f[R]
Disable coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enversion\f[R]
Show version.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]
Show help.
