.SH TIME MACHINE
Press \f[B]Left\f[R] to enter time\-machine mode, browsing historical
snapshots of command output.
Use \f[B]Left\f[R] / \f[B]Right\f[R] to navigate, \f[B]t\f[R] for an
overview, \f[B]Enter\f[R] to jump to a snapshot, and \f[B]Space\f[R] or
\f[B]Escape\f[R] to return to live mode.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Auto\-exit condition met, or manual quit with last child exit 0.
.TP
\f[I]N\f[R]
Last child process exit code (manual quit).
.TP
\f[B]125\f[R]
Usage error (bad arguments).
.TP
\f[B]126\f[R]
Command not executable.
.TP
\f[B]127\f[R]
Command not found.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B]NO_COLOR\f[R]
If set, disables coloured output (no\-color.org).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
peep git status

peep \-n 5 df \-h

peep \-w \(dqsrc/**/*.cs\(dq dotnet test

peep \-d kubectl get pods

peep \-\-exit\-on\-success \-\- dotnet build

peep \-\-exit\-on\-match \(dqREADY\(dq \-\- kubectl get pods

peep \-\-once \-\- docker ps
.EE
